metadata.name: Field Sketch #97
metadata.description:
Field Sketch

This is a 100% generative abstract project. I'm experimenting again with sketchy rough drawing and trying to create something that looks like it could have been created by hand. There are seven composition types that produce different styles of output.

This project uses the fx(params) WYSIWYG functionality so the minter will get exactly the output they configure.

Explanation of Numeric Params (all have range 0-100):

XBounds - low values have primary structures near the middle of the horizontal axis

YBounds - low values have primary structures near the middle of the vertical axis. For Quantized composition types this also affects the vertical level of the vanishing points.

StructureSmooth - low values have a more complex global structure

DetailSmooth - low values have a more complex fine structure

SegmentLength - low values have more but shorter lines drawn

AngleVariation - low values have more coherent line direction

ColorNoise - the higher the value the more random color variation for each line segment

Order - low values have the lines follow the flow fields in a more chaotic fashion

Blur - higher values will use blur on top and bottom of output to simulate depth of field

Symmetry - The possible values are no symmetry, 3, 4, 6, or 12. Any symmetry will be imperfect - it guides the construction of the composition but other random factors will usually prevent an exactly symmetrical result.

--------------------------

There are some keyboard operations available.

Click on the output and use these keys to affect it:
's' - save at current resolution
'2' - change to 2000 x 2000 resolution
'3' - change to 3000 x 3000 resolution
...
'8' - change to 8000 x 8000 resolution

Note that at higher resolutions there will be some minor variation in output.

Copyright 2023 Jeff Clark
--------------------------
100% generative

All drawing and geometric code created by Jeff Clark using standard javascript and canvas 2D api. Perlin noise was used with support from perlin.js at https://codepen.io/sixsided/pen/emxxea.js

metadata.name: CHX-1 #170
metadata.description:
Glitching pixels like it’s 1999.

Inspired by 90’s digital aesthetics, CHX-1 takes a random selection of GAN seeds, combines them in unique ways, and processes them –individually and as a group– with a series of glitching dithering algorithms. Generating fun, original, colorful artworks. Millions of possibilities. Have fun!

<<< Base seeds generated offline using personal styleGAN2-ADA models. Image processing and combinations done generatively by the CHX-1 algorithm >>>

GAN –> p5js –> Blockchain


• Artworks can take a few seconds to load when running live code.

• Press “s” (when "open live" is active) to save a PNG image.

metadata.name: Action; System #8
metadata.description:
Action; system is an experimental study inspired by the work of François Morellet. Morellet was one of the founders of the Groupe de Recherche d'Art Visuel (GRAV), founded in the 60s. His work was often informed by systems, a set of rules that determine the artwork, reducing the artist's subjectivity to a minimum.

This work explores what happens when we let go of the strict rule set. Do we ever fully let go?

-----------------
This work was released for the 2023 fundraising exhibition Cure3, and all of the proceeds and 1% of royalties will go to Parkinson's research funds. You can find more information at https://cure3.co.uk/.

-----------------
Controls
- R: new randomized output (the chances of recovering one of these outputs are very slim, that's what the next control is for)
- E: high-res output
- Double click: fullscreen

While you see the eye of Horus, your artwork is loading.

------------------
Made with p5.js & glsl
License: CC BY-NC-ND 4.0

metadata.name: A Bugged Forest #80
metadata.description:
A forest has stories to tell.
About times that were, about times that will be.
-
This project was minted in much unusual conditions. 
We gathered here, by 38 degrees heat. We belong to a crowd who loves stories, of civilisations at stake and deities, of afterlife and worship. We drank and hugged and chanted pagan hymns. We minted the Bugged Forest from our place on earth that we call Hell just for the fun of it. We are passionate, and loving, and angry and desperate. We, people of the soil, under a bugged sun.
-
This project is the long-form version of an algorithm that contains a bug. “The Bugged Tree”’s code was salvaged and stored and served as the core motivation and engine for an entire forest. Its concept is about releasing the control. I am a  byproduct of evolution, an iteration of that specie who wanted utter control, and which at some point, lost control over its own creation. As a generative artist, I chose to welcome the event of chance into my creative process. The symbolism in chance made me feel humble and free. Unwilling to make any change to a story that the Tree needed to tell me, as a listener, rather than a writer of my own idealised fantasies.
-
The iterations aren’t under control. They may be odd and off. We have to accept it. They are also plottable, press [s] in live mode to get a SVG. Attempt the plot at your own risk, as there’s a possibility for it to come near to impossibilities or cause paper or motor damage, and most certainly, a bugged drawing.
-
From Earth or from Hell, with love, yours truthfully, NFTBiker and zancan

metadata.name: Conspiracy Theory Vol.2: a letter #26
metadata.description:
This artwork is the result of my exploration in conceptual art and a continuation to one of my early works (conspiracy theory).

The idea was inspired by Conspiracy Walls. This work is an exploration in the philosophy of phenomenology to challenge our understanding of reality and truth and our attitude towards mental disorders and consciousness. What information does a folded letter give us? See the different variations of this token for a more complete understanding of the artwork. The text is based on psychological studies and their integration with various metaphors and references, unlike the previous work that used the text of Alice in Wonderland, to emphasize more on the phenomenological perspective and its connection with psychology, ambiguous and deep sentences that are randomly selected have been used. Is anyone really looking for the author of this letter? Can truth be different from reality? What is reality and what is its relationship with our perception of phenomena? These are some of the challenges that this artwork tries to create in our minds. 

----------- 

A few words about conceptual art and its relationship with this work and generative art:
Why should we value the combination of conceptual art with generative art? I've been dabbling in different styles of generative art for a while, and I've come to realize that conceptual art can add something to generative art. Conceptual art can bring the soul back to generative art and talk about deep concerns and concepts. As my friends have reminded me "art should speak" and this is very important in this regard and I hope this artwork will help in this matter. Share your thoughts about this artwork and this topic, it will always be a pleasure for me to read them.

Press ’s’ on the live mode to save the artwork with high resolution.

Made with P5js.

metadata.name: The Trap #133
metadata.description:
“Hell is empty and all the devils are here” - William Shakespeare. 
"There's only one hell, the one we live in now" - Red Woman | Game of Thrones. 

The symbolism of this abstraction is simple: something from above is watching you down here playing with your lives in the trap of the material world that it has created for your soul. But maybe it's a good trap, because it gives you the opportunity to make your own way and gives you your own will. After all, there is a possibility that outside this cage your individuality is erased, because you become a small part of some big one whole. The gloomy grid on top of the canvas symbolizes that trap (cage), bright or dark geometric figures (only circle, rectangle, triangle are used randomly) under it are our souls.

Kyiv, 08.2022.

metadata.name: Solitude Meditation #5
metadata.description:
"A room, a space, a solitude corner within the inner thought. Existed as a place to meditate and replenish the soul to be more at ease."

This piece means to mimic a sense of a dark room that contains radiated warm lights with subtle movement. It will follow the current resolution of the window where it is placed.

/////INTERACTIVITY/////
Do all the instructions below after opening the live mode.

1. To capture the screen, press the "c" button on your computer keyboard.

2. To save a 3-second .GIF from your iteration, press the "s" button on your computer keyboard. Please be patient while waiting for the piece to save and render its frames.

3. To adjust the piece resolution, you need to set your browser first and then reload the browser every time you want to capture the screen or save the rendered .GIF file.
///////////////////////

Created using Hydra and p5.js

Rangga Purnama Aji, 2022
https://linktr.ee/ranggapuraji
